{
  "text": "The reverse was seen in patient 11, who presented a decline in C-peptide levels after 1 year and resumed insulin use after that time. With the exception of patient 1, irrespective of insulin use all others achieved and maintained peak stimulated C-peptide levels greater than 0.60 ng/mL, which is known to be associated with reduced prevalence of diabetic complications. [CITATION_1] Area under the curve levels of C-peptide increased significantly after transplantation and remained high up to 24 months thereafter.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "24828719"
